, "text_ar": "وَاَحْمِى حَوْزَةَ الغَايِبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I guard from encroachment the property of the absent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning her"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroj", "text_ar": "فَرْج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which was the property of her husband by the marriage-contract: whence it appears that, if this saying be the only ground upon which Az has asserted that one of the significations of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawozapN", "text_ar": "حَوْزَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroj", "text_ar": "فَرْج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a woman, [as is also said in the K,] his assertion requires consideration; for a woman's"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "frj", "text_ar": "فرج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is her own when she has no husband; and when she is married, it is her husband's property. (L, TA.) You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaArafiY Hawozatihi", "text_ar": "صَارَفِى حَوْزَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Hawozihi", "text_ar": "فِى حَوْزِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fY Hay~izihi", "text_ar": "فى حَيِّزِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It became in his possession,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "occupation."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN maAniEN Hawozatahu", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ مَانِعٌ حَوْزَتَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one defends,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "guards, from encroachment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "invasion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "attack, what is in his"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hay~iz", "text_ar": "حَيِّز"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in his possession"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "occupation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) In like manner, a poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "HamaY HawozaAtihi faturikona qaforFA"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He guarded from encroachment his tracts of pasture-land"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that they were left deserted"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Fr, TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faHamaY HawozapF", "text_ar": "فَحَمَى حَوْزَةً"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_isolaAmi", "text_ar": "الاـِسْلَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And he defended,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "protected,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "guarded, from encroachment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "invasion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "attack, the limits,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what the limits comprised,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the territory,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the tracts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "regions, of El-Islám"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the Muslims"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawozapu Almuloki", "text_ar": "حَوْزَةُ المُلْكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies [in like manner]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayoDatuhu", "text_ar": "بَيْضَتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "te